1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,556
This series is crafted for
the purpose of entertainment.

2
00:00:02,580 --> 00:00:04,796
All characters, behaviours, settings, and events
depicted in this drama are entirely fictitious.

3
00:00:04,820 --> 00:00:06,636
They are not designed to allude to any particular
entity, occupation, or group of people.

4
00:00:06,660 --> 00:00:09,980
Viewer discretion is advised.

5
00:00:10,020 --> 00:00:13,086
[North Star Entertainment]

6
00:00:13,110 --> 00:00:14,980
[IQIYI]

7
00:00:15,150 --> 00:00:17,180
[Present]

8
00:00:19,550 --> 00:00:26,510
♫ Never met anyone who could
make me understand this word ♫

9
00:00:27,880 --> 00:00:34,780
♫ But when I met you, my
heart started beating fast ♫

10
00:00:36,010 --> 00:00:43,180
♫ You're the only one in my heart
who could make me feel this way ♫

11
00:00:44,380 --> 00:00:50,910
♫ This long-awaitied moment is now over ♫

12
00:00:52,080 --> 00:00:56,326
♫ From now on, my heart and soul
will be yours for the rest of my life ♫

13
00:00:56,350 --> 00:00:59,680
♫ Always have each other, never let go ♫

14
00:01:00,050 --> 00:01:04,726
♫ Trust in me 'cause I'll be by your side ♫

15
00:01:04,750 --> 00:01:09,756
♫ Hold my hand, Baby ♫

16
00:01:09,780 --> 00:01:12,976
[Desires in the Wind]

17
00:01:13,000 --> 00:01:15,776
[Previously] Our informant just tracked
that cop's phone and got her location.

18
00:01:15,800 --> 00:01:18,130
I got summoned to the hotel immediately.

19
00:01:18,300 --> 00:01:20,620
But according to the original
schedule, it's not tomorrow.

20
00:01:29,560 --> 00:01:30,800
What should we do?

21
00:01:31,460 --> 00:01:33,000
We have to find a new hideout.

22
00:01:33,800 --> 00:01:35,800
This is a national-level matter, Lom.

23
00:01:35,960 --> 00:01:37,460
Please don't tell Dad about this yet.

24
00:01:37,800 --> 00:01:41,300
But this is too big for
you to handle alone.

25
00:01:41,530 --> 00:01:45,326
This flower crown might
not be a perfect replacement.

26
00:01:45,350 --> 00:01:48,756
But as long as you are born a
princess, no matter where you are

27
00:01:48,780 --> 00:01:51,350
in my eyes-you'll always be a princess.

28
00:02:08,300 --> 00:02:10,610
Looking happy as if you're in love, huh?

29
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:13,750
Nonsense. Who's in love?

30
00:02:15,730 --> 00:02:20,410
Lom, you're not into Miss Blew, are you?

31
00:02:20,530 --> 00:02:24,686
What? Why would I like her?

32
00:02:24,710 --> 00:02:26,410
You're imagining things.

33
00:02:27,730 --> 00:02:30,400
Well, I'm relieved to hear that.

34
00:02:43,329 --> 00:02:45,860
So, have you thought about
what you would do next?

35
00:02:47,660 --> 00:02:48,660
Not yet.

36
00:02:50,400 --> 00:02:53,660
Then, why don't you just
stay here while you figure it out.

37
00:02:53,930 --> 00:02:57,126
The weather here is nice. We
also have many beautiful attractions.

38
00:02:57,150 --> 00:03:00,510
I'm sure Miss Blew will soon
definitely fall in love with Chiang Rai.

39
00:03:01,800 --> 00:03:04,130
I'd rather not bother you
and Miss Din that long.

40
00:03:05,730 --> 00:03:09,626
It's not a bother at all. Didn't
you say we're friends now?

41
00:03:09,650 --> 00:03:11,510
Friends must help each other.

42
00:03:12,600 --> 00:03:16,860
But I don't want to trouble you
and Miss Din with my problem.

43
00:03:19,329 --> 00:03:24,786
Miss Blew, I might look soft on the
outside but I'm actually quite tough.

44
00:03:24,810 --> 00:03:27,756
If there's anything we could do,

45
00:03:27,780 --> 00:03:30,480
Din and I would be more
than happy to help, right?

46
00:03:35,360 --> 00:03:39,050
But I still think you should
tell Uncle Thit about this, Lom.

47
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:47,810
He probably knows by now I've been missing.

48
00:03:48,160 --> 00:03:49,250
What?

49
00:03:49,610 --> 00:03:51,750
Lom disappeared and still
hasn't come back to work?

50
00:03:53,329 --> 00:03:56,926
She didn't come to report
herself and didn't show up at work.

51
00:03:56,950 --> 00:04:02,280
Her phone is also off. No one
can get ahold of her right now.

52
00:04:03,700 --> 00:04:06,660
This is serious. Why hasn't
anyone told me earlier?

53
00:04:09,900 --> 00:04:12,560
So, what do you want me to do, sir?

54
00:04:21,500 --> 00:04:24,660
That's all right. I'll take
care of it. Thanks a I.

55
00:04:38,500 --> 00:04:43,750
Khem, any update from our
informant where that damn cop is?

56
00:04:45,730 --> 00:04:48,836
They're working on it. We
should hear from them soon.

57
00:04:48,860 --> 00:04:50,180
[Gunshots]

58
00:04:59,560 --> 00:05:01,330
Mr. Henri!

59
00:05:09,360 --> 00:05:10,660
There you are.

60
00:05:14,000 --> 00:05:15,600
You messed up, didn't you?

61
00:05:16,400 --> 00:05:17,730
That's why you've disappeared.

62
00:05:18,600 --> 00:05:22,950
Well, sir…we…

63
00:05:23,930 --> 00:05:30,080
Haven't I already told you what
you'd face if you fail this job?

64
00:05:31,330 --> 00:05:33,710
This is all Khem's fault, sir.

65
00:05:37,060 --> 00:05:38,530
He's the one who messed up.

66
00:05:40,260 --> 00:05:47,010
I told him to keep an eye on the princess
but he was reckless and let her get away.

67
00:05:47,130 --> 00:05:49,426
Mr. Henri, I'm…I'm sorr.

68
00:05:49,450 --> 00:05:50,850
[Gunshot] Mr. Henri, I'm…I'm sorr-.

69
00:05:54,260 --> 00:05:56,750
Sir, please spare my life.

70
00:05:57,409 --> 00:05:59,286
Give me another chance.

71
00:05:59,310 --> 00:06:01,026
I promise I won't-.

72
00:06:01,050 --> 00:06:05,110
You maggots already got enough chances.

73
00:06:08,000 --> 00:06:11,010
If that bloody cop didn't
butt in and help the princess,

74
00:06:11,300 --> 00:06:13,510
I could've finished her long ago.

75
00:06:13,930 --> 00:06:19,680
That cop tricked me to track down her phone
to somewhere else. She got us all fooled.

76
00:06:20,960 --> 00:06:23,810
A cop? Who?

77
00:06:24,400 --> 00:06:27,410
Lieutenant Vayo Watinwanich.

78
00:06:32,300 --> 00:06:33,680
Just as I thought.

79
00:06:34,400 --> 00:06:37,310
Sir, what do you want me to do?

80
00:06:38,780 --> 00:06:40,650
You can just say it.

81
00:06:42,300 --> 00:06:43,500
Get rid of them.

82
00:06:44,600 --> 00:06:47,060
And bring me their dead
bodies as soon as you can.

83
00:06:48,659 --> 00:06:54,350
Or else it's you who'll be dead next.

84
00:07:00,530 --> 00:07:02,150
Blew is still alive?

85
00:07:02,900 --> 00:07:07,560
Yes. Those jerks messed up
and let the princess get away.

86
00:07:08,530 --> 00:07:11,500
They said a cop called
Vayo helped rescue her.

87
00:07:13,100 --> 00:07:16,286
I knew it. That damn
cop is definitely involved.

88
00:07:16,310 --> 00:07:18,980
That's why she has
disappeared for many days now.

89
00:07:19,060 --> 00:07:22,376
If the princess is still alive,
I'm out of this. I quit! I'm scared!

90
00:07:22,400 --> 00:07:23,450
Get a grip, Helena!

91
00:07:23,480 --> 00:07:26,210
No! If anything goes
wrong, you'll get us all killed!

92
00:07:27,100 --> 00:07:27,900
No!

93
00:07:28,100 --> 00:07:29,400
Don't be a coward.

94
00:07:30,310 --> 00:07:33,350
You are so close to having
the power in your hands.

95
00:07:33,500 --> 00:07:35,500
Are you going to throw it away like that?

96
00:07:36,560 --> 00:07:38,300
But the princess never gives up so easily.

97
00:07:39,100 --> 00:07:43,080
Even if she's still alive,
there's nothing she can do.

98
00:07:44,400 --> 00:07:46,880
Right now, it's us who
are holding the upper hand.

99
00:07:46,960 --> 00:07:48,560
We'll be flying off to Japan tomorrow.

100
00:07:52,060 --> 00:07:53,909
There's no need to fret.

101
00:08:02,530 --> 00:08:09,086
As for you, Henri. If those
hitmen can't do their job,

102
00:08:09,110 --> 00:08:11,256
send our men to finish the work instead.

103
00:08:11,280 --> 00:08:15,250
This shouldn't be a problem for
the head of royal guards like you.

104
00:08:15,500 --> 00:08:16,500
Hold on, Grace.

105
00:08:16,860 --> 00:08:19,660
Those men from Madelin still don't
know the princess has been swapped.

106
00:08:19,760 --> 00:08:21,360
If I send them to do this job,

107
00:08:21,730 --> 00:08:23,760
our plan will definitely get exposed.

108
00:08:24,000 --> 00:08:24,800
So what?

109
00:08:24,960 --> 00:08:28,060
Are you going to let the princess live?

110
00:08:28,660 --> 00:08:30,760
Or you suddenly got
chicken out like Helena?

111
00:08:35,900 --> 00:08:39,130
But they already promised they'd
bring me the cop's and princess's bodies.

112
00:08:39,200 --> 00:08:40,280
What if they mess up again?

113
00:08:45,660 --> 00:08:50,580
If that is so, I will crush
them with my own hands.

114
00:08:51,300 --> 00:08:53,800
And I'll clean up after everything myself.

115
00:09:07,060 --> 00:09:09,080
I trust you, darling.

116
00:09:10,660 --> 00:09:11,900
Don't let me down.

117
00:09:31,200 --> 00:09:33,160
Uncle Thit just called
and told me about you.

118
00:09:33,960 --> 00:09:36,530
I think he already knows you're here.

119
00:09:40,500 --> 00:09:42,260
Did he want you to send me home?

120
00:09:44,400 --> 00:09:49,326
No, he told me you got suspended…

121
00:09:49,350 --> 00:09:53,786
Because you disobeyed your supervisor's
order and neglected to perform your duties.

122
00:09:53,810 --> 00:09:57,156
If you don't clarify yourself or turn
yourself in for an internal investigation,

123
00:09:57,180 --> 00:10:01,450
you might get sacked and lose your badge.

124
00:10:03,200 --> 00:10:05,300
You know I can't turn back.

125
00:10:07,900 --> 00:10:10,960
Does that mean you're willing
to end your career for Miss Blew?

126
00:10:13,300 --> 00:10:17,880
Mhm. I'll do it if I have to.

127
00:10:19,560 --> 00:10:21,210
Listen, Lom.

128
00:10:21,860 --> 00:10:23,800
You can't handle this alone.

129
00:10:24,800 --> 00:10:27,260
And I'm not going to let
you risk your life like that too.

130
00:10:28,900 --> 00:10:31,300
Go ask Uncle Thit for
help. I'll help you talk to him.

131
00:10:31,860 --> 00:10:34,100
Can I try it on my own first?

132
00:10:36,260 --> 00:10:41,410
I don't want my decision to cause
Dad or our siblings any trouble.

133
00:10:43,050 --> 00:10:46,910
And I don't want to
ruin Dad's reputation too.

134
00:10:47,350 --> 00:10:49,480
He has spent a lifetime building it.

135
00:10:51,600 --> 00:10:56,510
Lom, you're not feeling
what you shouldn't, are you?

136
00:11:00,060 --> 00:11:02,260
I know what you want to say.

137
00:11:07,500 --> 00:11:11,280
About your feelings,
I've never said it's wrong.

138
00:11:12,130 --> 00:11:14,560
I always hope you'd find the
love you've been looking for,

139
00:11:15,260 --> 00:11:17,280
and be with someone who truly deserves you.

140
00:11:18,360 --> 00:11:24,710
But maybe it's better to never let your
feelings grow for someone out of your league.

141
00:11:29,600 --> 00:11:33,780
Even if you don't tell me,
I'm well aware where I belong.

142
00:11:35,330 --> 00:11:37,880
You know me, I'm not
a fan of disappointment.

143
00:11:39,530 --> 00:11:42,510
I just hope that one day
I'll also find that kind of love.

144
00:11:42,950 --> 00:11:47,380
Like how you've found
Rose, or Nam has found Lada.

145
00:11:50,960 --> 00:11:51,960
I know.

146
00:11:54,000 --> 00:11:58,100
Let's just say, I'm not going to fall for her.

147
00:11:59,100 --> 00:12:01,860
I'm not going to hope
for something I can't have.

148
00:12:03,400 --> 00:12:06,500
I'll keep reminding myself I'm
only doing this because it's my duty,

149
00:12:07,500 --> 00:12:08,610
okay?

150
00:12:11,500 --> 00:12:12,500
Okay.

151
00:12:29,000 --> 00:12:31,060
Your bouquet looks stunning, Miss Blew.

152
00:12:33,900 --> 00:12:35,660
Yours is also beautiful, Miss Rose.

153
00:12:39,760 --> 00:12:43,800
But compared to yours, mine
looks like one made by a child.

154
00:12:46,560 --> 00:12:52,080
Don't say that. Every flower
has its own unique beaut.

155
00:12:53,910 --> 00:12:55,280
That's sharp.

156
00:13:14,130 --> 00:13:16,100
Why are you standing over there, Lom?

157
00:13:28,260 --> 00:13:29,950
Will you excuse me for a moment?

158
00:13:30,660 --> 00:13:31,660
Yes.

159
00:13:38,060 --> 00:13:39,130
Miss Vayo!

160
00:13:41,160 --> 00:13:42,160
Miss Vayo!

161
00:13:43,860 --> 00:13:45,000
Can you hear me.

162
00:13:50,600 --> 00:13:51,960
Yes, Miss Blew?

163
00:13:53,560 --> 00:13:54,560
I have a question.

164
00:13:55,960 --> 00:13:56,960
Yes?

165
00:13:59,130 --> 00:14:00,130
Is it beautiful?

166
00:14:04,530 --> 00:14:06,130
Could I possibly say no?

167
00:14:07,300 --> 00:14:08,510
Absolutely not.

168
00:14:09,600 --> 00:14:11,100
What if I say yes?

169
00:14:11,600 --> 00:14:12,600
I'd be flattered.

170
00:14:14,500 --> 00:14:15,960
What if I say no?

171
00:14:16,660 --> 00:14:17,660
I'd be angry.

172
00:14:18,760 --> 00:14:20,180
Then, yes-it's beautiful.

173
00:14:20,900 --> 00:14:22,460
You don't need to try to please me.

174
00:14:25,300 --> 00:14:27,710
I was only telling the truth.

175
00:14:28,750 --> 00:14:36,650
Iris flower-captivating, yet
dangerous to one's heart.

176
00:14:40,800 --> 00:14:42,000
Dangerous? How?

177
00:14:44,960 --> 00:14:51,010
The closer you get, the more enticed you'd become.
So, you'd rather keep your distance from it.

178
00:14:59,500 --> 00:15:00,860
Why keep your distance?

179
00:15:06,260 --> 00:15:09,580
Oh, I forgot to tell you.

180
00:15:10,160 --> 00:15:15,280
Fah called this morning and said that your imposter has
changed her plan and flew off to Japan this morning.

181
00:15:18,360 --> 00:15:23,010
They probably know I'm still alive
and fear they might get exposed.

182
00:15:23,900 --> 00:15:29,280
That's why they're fleeing with the rest from Madelin
because they're afraid I might warn those people about them.

183
00:15:31,530 --> 00:15:35,650
That means there's still
someone we can trust.

184
00:15:37,160 --> 00:15:39,500
Not everyone in Madelin is a traitor.

185
00:15:40,100 --> 00:15:44,310
There are still royal guards who are willing to
sacrifice their lives to protect the royal family.

186
00:15:45,160 --> 00:15:47,180
But we still have to be careful though.

187
00:15:48,300 --> 00:15:51,260
Those men who tried to hurt you are Thai.

188
00:15:51,900 --> 00:15:54,600
I believe they will not
stop until their job is done.

189
00:15:57,960 --> 00:16:02,580
We have to get out of here fast. I
don't want to put your sister in danger.

190
00:16:03,900 --> 00:16:05,300
Please don't worry, Miss Blew.

191
00:16:06,560 --> 00:16:08,460
I will protect you with my own life.

192
00:16:12,130 --> 00:16:14,500
I promise you will
return to Madelin safely.

193
00:16:17,100 --> 00:16:19,200
You're not going to leave
me, are you, Miss Vayo?

194
00:16:27,060 --> 00:16:28,130
I promise.

195
00:16:29,160 --> 00:16:30,930
As long as you need me,

196
00:16:31,960 --> 00:16:33,160
I will never go anywhere.

197
00:16:59,800 --> 00:17:02,310
Din, are you waiting for someone?

198
00:17:15,200 --> 00:17:16,200
Dad!

199
00:17:18,160 --> 00:17:19,609
How did he get here?

200
00:17:20,560 --> 00:17:22,530
I told him to come.

201
00:17:24,960 --> 00:17:25,960
Lom!

202
00:17:31,760 --> 00:17:32,880
Your Highness!

203
00:17:49,660 --> 00:17:52,060
You're telling me that the
one here is the real princess?

204
00:17:52,110 --> 00:17:53,150
Yes.

205
00:17:54,160 --> 00:17:57,160
What about the princess who just left
our country this morning? Who is she?

206
00:17:57,660 --> 00:18:01,410
She's a fake one, Dad. She's an imposter.

207
00:18:02,060 --> 00:18:04,860
I can assure you that
Lom is telling the truth.

208
00:18:08,260 --> 00:18:11,550
The truth? And now what?

209
00:18:12,410 --> 00:18:13,980
Are you going to help the princess…

210
00:18:15,060 --> 00:18:22,506
And throw away your career and future so
easily without caring about the consequences?

211
00:18:22,530 --> 00:18:26,010
But aren't you the one who told
me to keep the princess safe?

212
00:18:26,410 --> 00:18:28,150
Have you forgotten, Dad?

213
00:18:31,100 --> 00:18:35,936
Fine. Then, I order you to
step down from this matter.

214
00:18:35,960 --> 00:18:37,160
Leave the princess.

215
00:18:37,560 --> 00:18:41,110
I'll talk to the officials in Madelin
and let them handle this from now on.

216
00:18:41,200 --> 00:18:43,506
This is like sending the
princess to face the danger alone.

217
00:18:43,530 --> 00:18:45,000
Isn't she already in danger now?

218
00:18:46,930 --> 00:18:48,550
I have only one daughter.

219
00:18:49,730 --> 00:18:52,010
I can't afford to lose you because of this.

220
00:18:53,500 --> 00:18:54,436
But…

221
00:18:54,460 --> 00:18:55,260
Lom!

222
00:18:55,460 --> 00:18:58,130
I think Uncle Thit is right.

223
00:18:58,700 --> 00:19:01,060
I know you want to protect Princess Blew,

224
00:19:01,860 --> 00:19:04,000
but this isn't something
you can handle alone.

225
00:19:08,730 --> 00:19:09,730
Please trust me.

226
00:19:11,000 --> 00:19:12,330
Let me take care of it.

227
00:19:13,400 --> 00:19:14,760
I will help the princess.

228
00:19:15,200 --> 00:19:16,280
And if anything goes wrong,

229
00:19:17,930 --> 00:19:19,300
I will take responsibility alone.

230
00:19:23,300 --> 00:19:29,456
But it took you blood, sweat, and
tears to be at this point in your career.

231
00:19:29,480 --> 00:19:31,320
Are you going to throw
it away just like that?

232
00:19:34,600 --> 00:19:42,600
I'm not throwing it away. But you…are
the most important thing in my life.

233
00:19:55,700 --> 00:20:00,180
I promise you-the princess will be safe.

234
00:20:49,300 --> 00:20:50,810
Greetings, Your Highness.

235
00:20:53,200 --> 00:20:54,460
Please be at ease.

236
00:21:02,100 --> 00:21:03,760
You are Miss Vayo's father.

237
00:21:05,180 --> 00:21:10,330
Yes, Your Highness. I am Police
General Wathit-Lom's father.

238
00:21:12,600 --> 00:21:16,800
I must apologise for putting your
daughter in a difficult situation.

239
00:21:18,500 --> 00:21:21,280
Lom has already told me
everything, Your Highness.

240
00:21:21,730 --> 00:21:23,660
I sincerely beg for your forgiveness.

241
00:21:24,400 --> 00:21:29,180
As a commander who has been reckless enough to
let such grave mistake occur during your visit,

242
00:21:31,130 --> 00:21:33,710
I shall solely take all the responsibilities.

243
00:21:37,200 --> 00:21:38,780
It is not your fault.

244
00:21:39,660 --> 00:21:42,930
It's my men who have created
a problem in your country.

245
00:21:47,200 --> 00:21:52,450
Please forgive me for being forthright, Your
Highness. I humbly beg for your gracious pardon.

246
00:21:57,130 --> 00:22:00,810
But I have only one daughter.

247
00:22:01,580 --> 00:22:05,680
And unfortunately, she
is affected by this matter.

248
00:22:06,300 --> 00:22:08,000
What happened to Miss Vayo?

249
00:22:09,600 --> 00:22:13,700
She has been suspended, and is
prone to be dismissed from her position.

250
00:22:17,600 --> 00:22:22,880
But that still means
nothing compared to her life.

251
00:22:23,910 --> 00:22:31,050
As a father, I'm afraid I cannot allow
my child to be in danger, Your Highness.

252
00:22:34,760 --> 00:22:36,240
Is there anything I could do to help?

253
00:22:36,800 --> 00:22:37,800
Please tell me.

254
00:22:41,560 --> 00:22:49,560
From now on, please let me take my daughter's place
as your bodyguard and be responsible for your safety.

255
00:22:51,110 --> 00:22:56,150
I will help act as a liaison and
inform Madelin about this matter.

256
00:22:58,410 --> 00:23:04,110
And I'd also like Lom to be
removed from this mission.

257
00:23:05,450 --> 00:23:12,610
I truly beg for your grace
and consent, Your Highness.

258
00:23:16,700 --> 00:23:22,500
I understand. I'm also concerned
and don't want her to risk her life for me.

259
00:23:24,330 --> 00:23:29,810
But right now, she
refuses to listen to anyone.

260
00:23:30,780 --> 00:23:38,780
Do you think you could possibly
talk to her for me, Your Highness?

261
00:23:47,660 --> 00:23:55,110
Certainly, I will talk to Miss Vayo and
have her convinced. Please do not worry.

262
00:23:59,060 --> 00:24:00,310
Thank you, Your Highness.

263
00:24:33,530 --> 00:24:36,660
[Din]: About Miss Blew, just let
your dad take care of her, trust me.

264
00:24:40,560 --> 00:24:48,560
It's not that I don't trust Dad. But those cops-his
subordinates and those around him-I don't trust any of them.

265
00:24:50,850 --> 00:24:56,680
Besides, I already gave Miss Blew
my word that I will always keep her safe.

266
00:24:59,330 --> 00:25:00,330
I don't want to risk it.

267
00:25:02,160 --> 00:25:06,700
But are you sure you'd be
able to look after her by yourself?

268
00:25:20,200 --> 00:25:28,200
[Wathit]: I have only one daughter. As a father, I'm afraid
I cannot allow my child to be in danger, Your Highness.

269
00:27:06,330 --> 00:27:08,160
General Wathit is in Chiang Rai?

270
00:27:09,330 --> 00:27:13,260
Does that mean his daughter
and the princess are there too?

271
00:27:17,500 --> 00:27:18,500
Okay.

272
00:27:22,360 --> 00:27:24,460
Tell our men to get ready.
We'll go to Chiang Rai.

273
00:27:24,860 --> 00:27:25,860
Yes, Boss.

274
00:27:28,060 --> 00:27:31,550
How dare she fooled me
around, running south to north.

275
00:27:48,760 --> 00:27:50,730
Do you want to talk to me, Miss Blew?

276
00:27:58,130 --> 00:27:59,200
Is it a secret?

277
00:28:00,860 --> 00:28:07,500
I appreciate everything you've done for me. But
from now on, you don't need to protect me anymore.

278
00:28:10,060 --> 00:28:11,130
What do you mean?

279
00:28:12,730 --> 00:28:14,600
Did my father tell you to do this?

280
00:28:15,930 --> 00:28:17,400
I'm going to talk to him.

281
00:28:20,100 --> 00:28:22,750
Do you really think he could make me?

282
00:28:23,860 --> 00:28:28,350
Nobody can change my mind except myself.

283
00:28:29,860 --> 00:28:30,900
I don't believe you.

284
00:28:33,260 --> 00:28:34,950
But I'm afraid it's true.

285
00:28:35,880 --> 00:28:41,010
From now on, the only help I
need would be from Mr. Wathit.

286
00:28:42,200 --> 00:28:44,300
But you were the one who asked me to help.

287
00:28:46,060 --> 00:28:51,480
Let's just say, I don't need
you in my life anymore.

288
00:28:55,160 --> 00:28:56,860
I hope you'd understand, Miss Vayo.

289
00:29:35,000 --> 00:29:37,930
Three armoured cars and the
security service have arrived.

290
00:29:38,100 --> 00:29:40,060
What about the safehouse? Is it ready?

291
00:29:40,300 --> 00:29:43,000
Yes, sir. We've kept it
confidential as instructed.

292
00:29:43,330 --> 00:29:48,730
Good. We'll use the route that doesn't stand
out. Tell everyone to make sure it's all clear.

293
00:29:49,160 --> 00:29:50,160
Yes, sir.

294
00:30:02,000 --> 00:30:03,330
It's time, Your Highness.

295
00:30:05,860 --> 00:30:07,260
Tell me your plan.

296
00:30:09,660 --> 00:30:16,480
I and the undercover officers will guard you out of here
and take you to the safehouse arranged for your safety.

297
00:30:16,960 --> 00:30:19,156
While you stay there,

298
00:30:19,180 --> 00:30:23,020
we will try to contact your father in Madelin and
inform him about the situation, Your Highness.

299
00:30:23,530 --> 00:30:25,930
I must warn you to be very cautious.

300
00:30:26,730 --> 00:30:31,450
Because right now, we do not
know who else is also with the traitors.

301
00:30:31,960 --> 00:30:34,110
I'm afraid Father might not be safe.

302
00:30:35,900 --> 00:30:39,050
Yes, Your Highness. I
shall proceed with caution.

303
00:30:39,460 --> 00:30:41,850
Everything has now been arranged.

304
00:30:42,130 --> 00:30:46,110
We can leave whenever
you're ready, Your Highness.

305
00:31:11,100 --> 00:31:14,950
Please stay safe and hope
all the traitors will get arrested.

306
00:31:16,800 --> 00:31:17,800
Thank you.

307
00:31:19,500 --> 00:31:24,380
When you finally return to your palace in Madelin,
please don't forget this friend of yours, Miss Blew.

308
00:31:26,260 --> 00:31:27,700
I shall never forget you, Miss Rose.

309
00:31:30,100 --> 00:31:36,250
Thank you for your warm welcome and wonderful
accommodation. I really like this place.

310
00:31:37,600 --> 00:31:42,300
It's our pleasure indeed. If there's a
chance, we do hope you'd come back here again.

311
00:31:43,530 --> 00:31:44,700
I certainly will.

312
00:31:50,360 --> 00:31:54,600
Din, where's Lom? Why isn't
she here to see Miss Blew off?

313
00:31:56,060 --> 00:31:58,650
I have no idea too. I haven't
seen her since this morning.

314
00:32:01,330 --> 00:32:03,760
I'll tell Buakiang to go look for her then.

315
00:32:05,400 --> 00:32:07,850
Please wait a moment, Miss Blew.

316
00:32:10,500 --> 00:32:16,060
Never mind, I have to go now. Please
say goodbye to Miss Vayo for me.

317
00:32:18,130 --> 00:32:19,700
Yes, I'll tell her.

318
00:32:54,960 --> 00:32:55,960
Goodbye, Your Highness.

319
00:32:56,080 --> 00:32:57,180
Goodbye.

320
00:33:52,910 --> 00:33:55,350
[Police]: We got ambushed, sir!

321
00:33:55,600 --> 00:33:59,010
Protect the princess! Please
stay down, Your Highness.

322
00:34:03,050 --> 00:34:04,580
[Hitman]: Go! Go! Go!

323
00:34:05,810 --> 00:34:07,710
[Gunfire]

324
00:34:14,949 --> 00:34:16,126
Let's go, Your Highness!

325
00:34:16,150 --> 00:34:17,480
[Hitman]: Get them!

326
00:34:37,330 --> 00:34:38,770
Please hang in there, Your Highness.

327
00:34:42,199 --> 00:34:43,199
Go!

328
00:34:48,300 --> 00:34:49,300
Keep going!

329
00:35:02,730 --> 00:35:04,310
Hide, Your Highness!

330
00:35:04,660 --> 00:35:05,680
Get down there.

331
00:35:14,010 --> 00:35:15,126
Mr. Wathit…

332
00:35:15,150 --> 00:35:16,410
Shhh!

333
00:35:29,600 --> 00:35:30,900
They'll probably be here soon.

334
00:35:31,600 --> 00:35:32,776
Please go first, Your Highness.

335
00:35:32,800 --> 00:35:34,360
But you'll be in danger.

336
00:35:36,530 --> 00:35:37,850
Let's go, Your Highness.

337
00:35:48,400 --> 00:35:49,530
Go!

338
00:36:10,110 --> 00:36:11,210
[Continuous gunfire]

339
00:36:31,100 --> 00:36:33,680
Hide and seek is over, Princess.

340
00:36:59,950 --> 00:37:01,480
[Gunshot]

341
00:37:22,260 --> 00:37:26,250
Miss Vayo…I'm scared.

342
00:37:27,150 --> 00:37:30,480
It's all right, Miss Blew. You're safe now.

343
00:37:41,900 --> 00:37:43,150
You're safe now.

344
00:37:55,600 --> 00:37:59,460
I'm sorry I lied to you.

345
00:38:01,000 --> 00:38:02,160
Lied about what?

346
00:38:04,130 --> 00:38:06,410
That I don't need you anymore.

347
00:38:12,460 --> 00:38:14,450
I need you, Vayo.

348
00:38:33,110 --> 00:38:35,080
[Gunfire]

349
00:38:42,730 --> 00:38:47,480
Drop the gun! Don't you dare turn around.

350
00:39:07,800 --> 00:39:11,910
Let's get out of here. More of
them will be coming. Let's go!

351
00:39:24,910 --> 00:39:25,980
Ouch!

352
00:39:26,100 --> 00:39:27,530
Are you okay, Miss Blew?

353
00:39:28,160 --> 00:39:29,280
I'm good.

354
00:39:39,900 --> 00:39:41,300
Someone's coming this way.

355
00:39:41,800 --> 00:39:43,150
What should we do?

356
00:39:43,730 --> 00:39:44,800
Let's hide.

357
00:39:47,930 --> 00:39:49,360
Let's go over there.

358
00:39:58,500 --> 00:40:01,880
Please stay here, Miss Blew.
I'll lure them to the other way.

359
00:40:02,100 --> 00:40:04,380
- But…
- Please trust me.

360
00:40:37,100 --> 00:40:38,180
Dad!

361
00:40:42,800 --> 00:40:44,530
I'm glad you're safe.

362
00:40:46,700 --> 00:40:48,810
Please forgive me, Your Highness.

363
00:40:49,180 --> 00:40:52,680
You have trusted me and
placed your safety in my care.

364
00:40:52,980 --> 00:40:59,680
But I failed to protect you
and put you in grave danger.

365
00:41:00,330 --> 00:41:03,660
It is not your fault. You already
did your best to protect me.

366
00:41:06,560 --> 00:41:08,480
Do you believe me now, Dad?

367
00:41:09,160 --> 00:41:11,780
That you can't follow the
protocol for this matter.

368
00:41:12,600 --> 00:41:15,310
There are Madelin's spies among the cops.

369
00:41:19,200 --> 00:41:20,710
I get it now.

370
00:41:21,300 --> 00:41:22,800
I'll keep my word.

371
00:41:23,600 --> 00:41:25,400
I'll respect your decision this time.

372
00:41:26,860 --> 00:41:28,600
We can't trust anyone right now.

373
00:41:29,000 --> 00:41:31,200
Madelin has sent their spies
to disguise among us cops.

374
00:41:31,330 --> 00:41:32,900
That's why they know my every move.

375
00:41:33,460 --> 00:41:35,730
And soon, they'll find out
where Miss Blew is hiding.

376
00:41:36,260 --> 00:41:37,930
Your method is definitely not safe.

377
00:41:39,760 --> 00:41:44,186
But we still have to stick to the
protocol. As for your concern,

378
00:41:44,210 --> 00:41:48,310
I'll be very cautious and make
sure only a few of us know about it.

379
00:41:48,860 --> 00:41:50,986
Then, can you promise me?

380
00:41:51,010 --> 00:41:55,556
That if your way doesn't work
out, you have to let me handle it.

381
00:41:55,580 --> 00:42:00,010
If you promise, I'll let
Miss Blew go with you.

382
00:42:02,500 --> 00:42:03,500
Okay.

383
00:42:09,400 --> 00:42:12,530
That's why you weren't there to see me off.

384
00:42:14,900 --> 00:42:18,350
That's right. I was worried
so I kept following behind.

385
00:42:21,400 --> 00:42:26,730
You'd better take the princess and hurry off now
before my subordinates will come and find you.

386
00:42:27,400 --> 00:42:28,680
What about you, Dad?

387
00:42:29,260 --> 00:42:31,860
Just leave it to me. Go now!

388
00:42:32,960 --> 00:42:33,960
Let's go, Miss Blew.

389
00:42:35,730 --> 00:42:36,730
Thank you.

390
00:42:38,200 --> 00:42:40,710
My pleasure, Your Highness. Please hurry.

391
00:43:06,160 --> 00:43:07,460
What's going on, girl?

392
00:43:08,460 --> 00:43:10,460
Can you give us a lift into town, Uncle?

393
00:43:10,800 --> 00:43:13,526
Oh, sure! Hop on.

394
00:43:13,550 --> 00:43:16,680
Not many vegetables today.
There's still some room left. Hop on!

395
00:43:16,860 --> 00:43:17,860
Okay!

396
00:44:22,560 --> 00:44:25,186
Sir, we've arrested five suspects.

397
00:44:25,210 --> 00:44:28,626
Six were shot dead. The rest can escape.

398
00:44:28,650 --> 00:44:31,626
Some officers got injured
during the shootout.

399
00:44:31,650 --> 00:44:35,080
We're waiting for the ambulance
to take them to the hospital.

400
00:44:35,200 --> 00:44:37,350
Send someone to keep
watch at the hospital too.

401
00:44:37,560 --> 00:44:39,530
Don't let the suspect escape.

402
00:44:40,330 --> 00:44:40,957
Yes, sir.

403
00:44:40,981 --> 00:44:46,950
The rest of our team are now searching the area
but the princess is still nowhere to be found.

404
00:44:52,130 --> 00:44:53,530
Let's call off the search.

405
00:44:56,530 --> 00:44:58,306
But the princess is still missing.

406
00:44:58,330 --> 00:45:02,610
If we can't find her by tonight,
I'm afraid she'd be in great danger.

407
00:45:03,960 --> 00:45:04,960
Just do as I said.

408
00:45:05,860 --> 00:45:06,860
Yes, sir.

409
00:45:26,960 --> 00:45:28,080
We're getting off here.

410
00:45:42,460 --> 00:45:43,730
That's it, girls.

411
00:45:44,060 --> 00:45:45,060
Thank you.

412
00:45:45,200 --> 00:45:47,160
Have a safe trip. Good luck.

413
00:46:03,250 --> 00:46:04,480
Let's go.

414
00:46:05,200 --> 00:46:06,330
Where are we going?

415
00:46:06,960 --> 00:46:09,180
My other sister's house in Hua Hin.

416
00:46:09,460 --> 00:46:10,810
Nam's house, right?

417
00:46:11,530 --> 00:46:13,300
How did you know?

418
00:46:13,500 --> 00:46:15,110
I've never told you about her.

419
00:46:15,160 --> 00:46:18,180
When we were in Chiang Rai,
Miss Rose told me everything.

420
00:46:18,400 --> 00:46:19,530
How are we getting there?

421
00:46:20,060 --> 00:46:21,060
Hitchhiking.

422
00:46:23,200 --> 00:46:24,200
Hitchhiking?

423
00:46:24,880 --> 00:46:28,750
Don't you have any cash on you?
Why can't we just take the bus?

424
00:46:29,960 --> 00:46:33,250
Well, this way we can go unnoticed
and won't draw any attention.

425
00:46:33,460 --> 00:46:37,080
Besides, they probably never expect
someone like you to be hitchhiking.

426
00:46:37,960 --> 00:46:43,080
I also never expected I'd be on
a truck loaded with vegetables.

427
00:46:43,450 --> 00:46:45,510
Is there still anything harsher than that?

428
00:46:46,360 --> 00:46:49,160
I'll try to find something better
than the vegetable truck this time.

429
00:47:07,960 --> 00:47:11,310
Is this your definition of 'better
than a vegetable truck', Miss Vayo?

430
00:47:12,530 --> 00:47:19,110
Yes! At least, you'll always have
something to eat along the way, Miss Blew.

431
00:47:41,300 --> 00:47:42,950
I'm feeling famished.

432
00:47:44,500 --> 00:47:45,860
That's good. Enjoy it.

433
00:47:47,960 --> 00:47:49,800
After you finish, let's get some sleep.

434
00:47:50,330 --> 00:47:52,850
It's still a long way to go. I'll
wake you up when we're there.

435
00:48:02,330 --> 00:48:04,050
- Is it good?
- Mhm!

436
00:48:05,600 --> 00:48:06,910
Eat as much as you want.

437
00:48:29,160 --> 00:48:33,500
[Din]: Uncle Thit said Lom is on her way to
see you. She should be there by tomorrow.

438
00:48:34,060 --> 00:48:35,980
[Nam]: How should I contact her then?

439
00:48:36,410 --> 00:48:40,510
If her phone is being tapped, that
means she can't use her phone right now.

440
00:48:42,760 --> 00:48:46,486
She'll manage to find
a way to get in touch.

441
00:48:46,510 --> 00:48:49,550
Just stay alert and be ready.

442
00:48:50,530 --> 00:48:55,150
Okay. Please tell Uncle Thit not to
worry. I'll take care of Lom for him.

443
00:49:17,600 --> 00:49:21,250
Miss Blew. Miss Blew.

444
00:49:27,130 --> 00:49:28,710
We've arrived in Prachuap.

445
00:49:50,000 --> 00:49:51,520
Uncle, thank you so much for the lift.

446
00:49:51,600 --> 00:49:52,880
You're welcome.

447
00:49:53,130 --> 00:49:55,100
Can I borrow your phone for a second?

448
00:49:55,460 --> 00:49:56,480
Sure.

449
00:49:58,660 --> 00:49:59,660
Thank you.

450
00:50:07,730 --> 00:50:11,080
Miss Blew, this is Lada-Nam's wife.

451
00:50:13,100 --> 00:50:15,060
And this is Fai, my little sister.

452
00:50:20,550 --> 00:50:22,960
Oh, please feel free to be casual.

453
00:50:25,100 --> 00:50:26,100
Yes.

454
00:50:29,560 --> 00:50:31,600
How come you're here too?

455
00:50:32,130 --> 00:50:35,680
Well, I'm worried about you. I came
straight here once I heard about it.

456
00:50:36,400 --> 00:50:38,200
I'm so touched.

457
00:50:46,500 --> 00:50:49,330
I'm truly grateful for all
of your help and support.

458
00:50:49,960 --> 00:50:51,510
You're welcome.

459
00:50:52,780 --> 00:50:58,410
It's been our pleasure to help you,
Your Highness-I mean-Miss Blew.

460
00:51:02,100 --> 00:51:04,880
You must be exhausted from a long trip.

461
00:51:05,280 --> 00:51:07,636
We've already arranged your accommodation.
Why don't you go get some rest?

462
00:51:07,660 --> 00:51:08,660
Thank you.

463
00:51:10,200 --> 00:51:16,910
Well then, I'll take you to your room, Miss
Blew. Let the siblings do their sister's talk.

464
00:51:19,330 --> 00:51:21,100
Please keep her company for a while.

465
00:51:22,700 --> 00:51:25,780
Miss Blew, I just need a few
minutes and will be with you shortly.

466
00:51:31,900 --> 00:51:32,950
This way, please.

467
00:51:46,860 --> 00:51:50,360
The princess looks so gorgeous in person.

468
00:51:50,800 --> 00:51:55,050
Now I know why you're willing
to give it all to protect her.

469
00:51:58,760 --> 00:52:01,920
It's a matter of life and death but you
still have the nerve to tease her, huh?

470
00:52:05,960 --> 00:52:07,050
Please come in.

471
00:52:16,700 --> 00:52:20,480
This place is very private
so please don't worry.

472
00:52:21,360 --> 00:52:25,610
Thank you. It's so beautiful.

473
00:52:27,560 --> 00:52:29,726
This room has a history too.

474
00:52:29,750 --> 00:52:34,880
Din and Rose used this house and
this room as their honeymoon place.

475
00:52:35,360 --> 00:52:37,960
You could say it's a room
that brings luck in love.

476
00:52:39,130 --> 00:52:45,286
Really? I wasn't surprised at first when I
learned Miss Din and Miss Rose are a couple.

477
00:52:45,310 --> 00:52:48,410
Until I met you and Miss Nam.

478
00:52:51,700 --> 00:52:56,580
Does that mean all of the sisters
in this family are in love with girls?

479
00:52:57,800 --> 00:53:02,150
Actually, Fai has never been with anyone.

480
00:53:02,460 --> 00:53:04,160
She doesn't seem to care about love.

481
00:53:05,130 --> 00:53:06,850
Probably much worse than Nam.

482
00:53:08,530 --> 00:53:10,100
What about Miss Vayo?

483
00:53:11,360 --> 00:53:13,250
Lom is also into girls.

484
00:53:14,160 --> 00:53:15,950
Into girls?

485
00:53:16,930 --> 00:53:24,930
Of all the four siblings, Lom has always been clear
that she likes women, especially beautiful women.

486
00:53:29,060 --> 00:53:32,160
Does that mean she used to date women?

487
00:53:34,100 --> 00:53:35,760
Well, sort of.

488
00:53:36,260 --> 00:53:41,350
Well, sort of. But I've never seen
her date anyone seriously though.

489
00:53:45,200 --> 00:53:47,780
Why would you want to
know about this, Miss Blew?

490
00:53:49,400 --> 00:53:50,400
Nothing.

491
00:53:51,210 --> 00:53:53,610
I see.

492
00:53:54,730 --> 00:53:58,250
I've prepared all the amenities
and everything you might need.

493
00:53:58,760 --> 00:54:02,150
If there's anything else you need,
please feel free to let me know.

494
00:54:03,200 --> 00:54:04,200
Thank you.

495
00:54:05,400 --> 00:54:08,950
Well then, please make
yourself comfortable.

496
00:54:13,000 --> 00:54:14,440
Please call me if you need anything.

497
00:54:26,700 --> 00:54:30,080
Here. It has a new SIM card
so you won't be tapped this time.

498
00:54:30,160 --> 00:54:31,160
Thanks.

499
00:54:34,760 --> 00:54:41,480
By the way, Din said Uncle Thit caught one of the
guys who tried to ambush the princess yesterday.

500
00:54:43,930 --> 00:54:47,730
But he's now in a hospital. Once he can
talk, Uncle Thit will go interrogate him.

501
00:54:48,700 --> 00:54:52,650
Wow, if Uncle Thit is going to do it himself,
we'll surely get a lot of information.

502
00:54:54,730 --> 00:54:56,510
I don't think it'd be that easy.

503
00:54:56,800 --> 00:54:59,040
No matter how hard Dad
tries to squeeze for information,

504
00:54:59,130 --> 00:55:02,260
that guy would never
say who the last boss is.

505
00:55:07,130 --> 00:55:09,660
So, now what?

506
00:55:12,200 --> 00:55:16,700
Considering Miss Blew's situation right now,
all I could do is hide her in a safe place.

507
00:55:19,600 --> 00:55:21,330
Where do you think would be safe for her?

508
00:55:35,730 --> 00:55:37,280
On your island.

509
00:55:39,730 --> 00:55:41,160
Your private island, Fai.

510
00:55:43,100 --> 00:55:44,380
That's right!

511
00:55:44,500 --> 00:55:46,350
It's far and hard to get there.

512
00:55:46,460 --> 00:55:47,500
Nobody knows about it too.

513
00:55:48,260 --> 00:55:50,650
Should we leave
tonight? I'll take care of it.

514
00:55:52,100 --> 00:55:55,786
Maybe not tonight. Miss
Blew wants to talk to Fah first.

515
00:55:55,810 --> 00:55:57,780
She needs Fah to help her with something.

516
00:55:59,130 --> 00:56:02,800
Okay. In the meantime, I'll arrange what you
and Miss Blew might need to travel there.

517
00:56:10,660 --> 00:56:14,110
Sorry to trouble you all.

518
00:56:16,400 --> 00:56:19,650
Hey, don't say that. I'm happy to help.

519
00:56:20,760 --> 00:56:22,310
All of us are happy to help.

520
00:56:22,930 --> 00:56:25,050
That's what sisters are for.

521
00:56:31,400 --> 00:56:36,756
But honestly, now that I've met the princess
in person, I also want to be her bodyguard.

522
00:56:36,780 --> 00:56:40,150
If you happen to need a backup,
you can always tell me, Sis.

523
00:56:42,600 --> 00:56:47,380
Fai, that's not funny. You
should know your place.

524
00:56:58,330 --> 00:57:02,080
I'll just…go check on Miss Blew then.

525
00:57:04,760 --> 00:57:08,350
Huh? Just like that?

526
00:57:10,860 --> 00:57:13,260
Do you know why she suddenly left?

527
00:57:14,400 --> 00:57:15,400
Why?

528
00:57:16,060 --> 00:57:18,460
Because you said
something that hit her nerve.

529
00:57:21,360 --> 00:57:22,510
What did I say?

530
00:57:24,060 --> 00:57:25,880
Seriously, you can't tell?

531
00:57:27,400 --> 00:57:31,550
But of course, you only
have eyes for Chonlada.

532
00:57:34,900 --> 00:57:35,900
I don't get it.

533
00:57:37,530 --> 00:57:42,310
Forget it. It's good that you only
live for your work and your wife.

534
00:57:44,530 --> 00:57:48,810
What the heck?

535
00:58:21,600 --> 00:58:23,200
Do you have any updates?

536
00:58:25,930 --> 00:58:26,960
Miss Vayo?

537
00:58:36,460 --> 00:58:37,500
Miss Vayo.

538
00:58:38,730 --> 00:58:39,730
Miss Vayo!

539
00:58:41,200 --> 00:58:43,750
Yes! What is it?

540
00:58:45,360 --> 00:58:48,350
I asked you if there's any updates.

541
00:58:48,700 --> 00:58:51,986
Oh, my father said the
suspects have been arrested.

542
00:58:52,010 --> 00:58:56,556
As for now, we just have to wait for
Fah, then we'll go to Fai's private island.

543
00:58:56,580 --> 00:59:00,480
If you want to contact anyone in Madelin,
it might be safer to let Fah do it for you.

544
00:59:14,200 --> 00:59:16,400
Can I take a walk by the beach?

545
00:59:19,160 --> 00:59:21,080
Of course, I'll go with you.

546
00:59:27,100 --> 00:59:30,656
This area is a private
zone. No one can enter.

547
00:59:30,680 --> 00:59:35,180
Nam already told her staff to guard the area, so that
we'll have enough time to run if anything happens.

548
00:59:36,760 --> 00:59:41,180
Your sisters seem to love
and worry about you a lot.

549
00:59:42,360 --> 00:59:49,686
That's right. We're really close because we grew
up together and our fathers are also siblings.

550
00:59:49,710 --> 00:59:53,550
That's why our names
rhyme-Din, Nam, Lom, and Fai.

551
00:59:54,960 --> 00:59:58,710
Why didn't Father name me
and my brother like that too?

552
00:59:59,160 --> 01:00:00,980
What's your brother's name, Miss Blew?

553
01:00:01,650 --> 01:00:04,110
Karel Jean De Laina.

554
01:00:04,730 --> 01:00:06,280
That sounds so cool.

555
01:00:06,800 --> 01:00:10,130
It feels strong like a prince in a movie.

556
01:00:12,960 --> 01:00:15,300
You understand the Madelin language?

557
01:00:15,800 --> 01:00:19,930
How did you know Karel
means strong and masculine?

558
01:00:22,730 --> 01:00:25,610
No, I don't. Just a lucky guess.

559
01:00:28,900 --> 01:00:34,450
Then, can you guess what my name
means? Catherine Blew De Laina.

560
01:00:35,330 --> 01:00:39,600
Does it mean strength,
endurance, and elegance?

561
01:00:41,930 --> 01:00:44,250
That's the meaning of an Iris flower.

562
01:00:46,050 --> 01:00:49,750
Please tell me, I don't
think I'll ever get it right.

563
01:00:51,930 --> 01:00:54,550
Catherine means pure and innocent.

564
01:00:55,010 --> 01:00:59,380
Father gave me this name because he
wants me to have a pure and innocent heart…

565
01:00:59,780 --> 01:01:04,050
And always be righteous and kind to others.

566
01:01:05,660 --> 01:01:08,860
And does 'Blew' simply
mean the blue colour?

567
01:01:10,130 --> 01:01:11,130
No.

568
01:01:12,800 --> 01:01:17,000
It's B-L-E-W, not blue.

569
01:01:18,760 --> 01:01:23,880
The one that means blowing
or making the wind blow?

570
01:01:24,960 --> 01:01:25,960
Yes.

571
01:01:27,760 --> 01:01:30,980
Looks like our names might
have the same meaning.

572
01:01:32,200 --> 01:01:33,380
They do, right?

573
01:02:01,330 --> 01:02:03,150
[NEXT EPISODE]
Did you just kiss someone?

574
01:02:03,810 --> 01:02:06,650
Are you falling for the princess now?

575
01:02:06,730 --> 01:02:09,156
If she's the one, just go for it.

576
01:02:09,180 --> 01:02:10,780
What are you waiting for?

577
01:02:13,800 --> 01:02:17,480
Can shooting for the first time
make my heart race this fast?

578
01:02:17,600 --> 01:02:19,330
So, see you at the pier, Sis.

579
01:02:19,560 --> 01:02:20,680
Have a safe trip.

580
01:02:21,100 --> 01:02:24,636
Excuse me, what is my
older sister-Fai-doing?

581
01:02:24,660 --> 01:02:25,810
She's already in bed, Miss.

582
01:02:27,060 --> 01:02:28,110
Thank you.

583
01:02:35,810 --> 01:02:40,256
♫ From now on, my heart and soul
will be yours for the rest of my life ♫

584
01:02:40,280 --> 01:02:43,550
♫ Always have each other, never let go ♫

585
01:02:44,310 --> 01:02:48,726
♫ Trust in me 'cause I'll be by your side ♫

586
